attribute.description: Onboard spatial average of NxN set of pixels, where N is the value of the keyword. SPATIAL_SUMMING = 1 implies that no spatial averaging has been applied to the image. .

PermissibleValue.valueMeaning: The commanded time delay integration was disabled.
The commanded time delay integration was enabled.

attribute.title: uncorrected_sclk_start_count
attribute.description: The spacecraft clock value (in seconds) when the instrument was commanded to acquire an observation. This can differ from the spacecraft_clock_start_count by as much as 4 seconds, depending on which bands are acquired in the image.

attribute.title: upload_id
attribute.description: The upload_id attribute describes a spacecraft command set that is associated with the given data product.

attribute.title: data_quality_desc
attribute.description: The data_quality_desc attribute describes the data qualities associated with a data_quality_id attribute.

attribute.title: data_quality_id
attribute.description: The data_quality_id attribute provides a numeric key which identifies the quality of data available for a particular time period. The data_quality_id scheme is unique to a given instrument and is described by the associated data_quality_desc attribute.

attribute.title: mission_phase_name
attribute.description: The mission_phase_name identifies a time period within the mission.

attribute.title: orbit_number
attribute.description: The orbit_number attribute identifies the number of the orbital revolution of the spacecraft around a target body. This value can optionally be set to 0 for cruise images or not set at all.

attribute.title: producer_institution_name
attribute.description: The producer_institution_name attribute identifies a university, research center, NASA center, or other institution associated with the production of a data product.

attribute.title: product_type
attribute.description: _TBD

attribute.title: product_version_id
attribute.description: The product_version_id attribute identifies the version of an individual data product.

attribute.title: rationale_desc
attribute.description: The rationale_desc attribute describes the rationale for performing a particular observation.

attribute.title: release_number
attribute.description: Release_number is the number of a scheduled release of data from PDS. The first data release would be Release 1. The release_number for a given product is always the first release in which it appears, and does not change if the product is revised later.

attribute.title: spacecraft_clock_count_partition
attribute.description: The spacecraft_clock_count_partition attribute indicates the clock partition active for the spacecraft_clock_start_count and spacecraft_clock_stop_count attributes.

attribute.title: spacecraft_clock_start_count
attribute.description: The spacecraft_clock_start_count attribute provides the value of the spacecraft clock at the actual start of image acquisition. There may be small inconsistencies with start_date_time due to varying correlation between UTC and the spacecraft clock. For purposes of data analysis the spacecraft clock value should be used. The format of this field is compatible with the NAIF Toolkit software where s = seconds converted from the clock's coarse counter and m = seconds converted from the clock's fine counter.

attribute.title: spacecraft_clock_stop_count
attribute.description: The spacecraft_clock_stop_count attribute provides the value of the spacecraft clock at the actual end of image acquisition. There may be small inconsistencies with stop_date_time due to varying correlation between UTC and the spacecraft clock. For purposes of data analysis the spacecraft clock value should be used. The format of this field is compatible with the NAIF Toolkit software where s = seconds converted from the clock's coarse counter and m = seconds converted from the clock's fine counter.
